#=GF CC   This entry represents an alpha-hairpin found at the N-terminal
#=GF CC   of Diadenylate cyclase CdaS. CdaS is one of 3 paralogous
#=GF CC   diadenylate cyclases (DAC) in Bacillus subtilis and B.
#=GF CC   thuringiensis, catalysing he condensation of 2 ATP molecules
#=GF CC   into cyclic di-AMP (c-di-AMP). It has slow DAC activity with ADP
#=GF CC   as a substrate and may have weak ADPase activity [1]. CdaS is
#=GF CC   required for efficient spore formation in B.thuringiensis,
#=GF CC   whereas in B.subtilis, it is required for efficient spore
#=GF CC   germination. It is produced under the control of different sigma
#=GF CC   factors in the two bacteria. It is also required for parasporal
#=GF CC   crystal formation [1-3].
